snippet.textDisplay:
I think DUN DUN (EVERGLOW) is seem similar to Young Gods (Total Ape), especially in this part: 0:54 -> 0:57 (DD) and 0:41 -> 0:44 (YG).
The chorus and the beat are a little bit alike too -_-
Last year, EVERGLOW was suspected of plagiarism of Kill This Love (BLACKPINK) and I was really angry and disappointed (I'm not a BLINK): There's still no official decision has been made yet but I found out that the beat of the beginning of Adios's (0:34 -> 0:46) really familiar to the beat of Kill This Love (https://youtu.be/39_1ndYigtE) - the BEAT, not the music! And about the line's orders are the same too (Intro - Rap; Chorus - Rap)!

Girls are beautiful but I still can't deny that truth: EVERGLOW was, and they're still plagiarism!


P/S: My English's not really good (or pretty bad and silly), sorry:/

snippet.textDisplay:
I am not a fan but i listen to this every damn day. You guys had such a bop here that you could all promote for your queens but you all waste your energy ripping each other's throat just because of line distribution.

This is just their third comeback, their producers and company can do more and so much better on their upcoming comebacks. They'll learn, and other members will shine in their own time. Whatever their line distribution is they did that because the producers believe that was the best for the song and the overall quality. Now if you don't agree that's up to you but you could just focus on uplifting such group with so much potential and focus and getting them more known and giving them a win rather than bringing them down yourselves. After this promotion then begin saying what you think should happen on their next comeback. Geez. You guys are wasting such good song and comeback. Please focus on promoting this group.

snippet.textDisplay:
I think DUN DUN (EVERGLOW) is seem similar to Young Gods (Total Ape), especially in this part: 0:54 -> 0:57 (DD) and 0:41 -> 0:44 (YG).
The chorus are a little but alike too -_-
Last year, EVERGLOW was suspected of plagiarism of Kill This Love (BLACKPINK) and I was really angry and disappointed (I'm not a BLINK): There's still no official decision has been made yet but I found out that the beat of the beginning of Adios's (0:34 -> 0:46) really familiar to the beat of Kill This Love (https://youtu.be/39_1ndYigtE) - the BEAT, not the music! And about the line's orders are the same too (Intro - Rap; Chorus - Rap)!
Girls are beautiful but I still can't deny that truth: EVERGLOW was, and they're still plagiarism!


P/S: My English's not really good (or pretty bad and silly), sorry:/
